#Text=( ( WS ) ) In some sources it says you are running for the Green Party nomination , while in others it says you are running as an Independent . Let 's clear this up , are you running for any particular party 's nomination , or as an Independent ?
#Text=( ( JS ) ) I have primarily run as an independent candidate during these four election cycles .
#Text=And I am currently running as an independent candidate now .
#Text=However , in 2007
#Text=I vied for the presidential nomination with the Green Party .
#Text=I did n't get their nomination , yet I continued to run in the 2008 election as an independent candidate .
#Text=For campaign 2012 , I might vie for the Green Party nomination again , once their Primary process starts .
#Text=Or , and this is another possibility , there has been some talk over the years of a “ fusion candidacy ” among Third Parties .

#Text=That is , say , the Constitution Party , the Green Party , the Libertarian Party ... would all get behind a single presidential candidate to increase the chances of a Third Party candidate winning .
#Text=If this evolves , I would consider vying for that kind of candidacy as well .
#Text=Running with a Party increases your chances of getting ballot access exponentially .
#Text=( ( WS ) ) How large is your campaign ?
#Text=( ( JS ) ) In comparison to the size of most major two Party campaigns , I once told a network news show in Indianapolis , in response to a similar question about our size :
#Text=“ Think the movie Hoosiers . ”
#Text=This , by the way , played well in Indiana .
#Text=Has your campaign received any notable endorsements ?
#Text=( ( JS ) ) Bill Samuels , president of the organization Consistent Life , has personally endorsed us in several campaigns .
#Text=( Consistent Life embodies valuing the sanctity of life at all stages from the “ womb to the tomb ” and is a network uniting organizations and individuals who support a consistent life ethic .

#Text=Their issues revolve around improving a spectrum of issues from poverty , to healthcare , to abortion , to global warming ... and anything else that has the potential to end life prematurely . ) “ [ Schriner ] is a Christian who is running as a consistent life ethic candidate .
#Text=He is right on all the life issues on which Obama is wrong , ” Samuel wrote in 2008 … Then there have been the media endorsements .
#Text=Some examples : “ ... he ( Schriner ) seems to make a lot more sense than most politicians I try not to listen to . ”
#Text=Steve Zender , editor , The Progressor-Times newspaper , Carey .
#Text=“ Is n't our generation ready to truly make our world better ?
#Text=The first step ?
#Text=Vote for Joe ! ” Leah Beth Bryson , columnist for The Vision student newspaper , Lambuth University .
#Text=“ A lot of what Joe says really would come across as good , common sense to many Americans .
#Text=They would gladly have someone like him leading the country ... ” -- editor David Green , The Observer , Morenci .

#Text=Then there have been all the ' average Joe ' endorsements – ' notable ' to us – from around the U.S. The following are a smattering of excerpts from a few of these comments ( which came in e-mails and letters ) :
#Text=“ Just wanted you to know that I 'm really impressed with all the research on a variety of local initiatives Mr. Schriner has done .
#Text=I was looking for a candidate I could actually support , and I found one here . ” -- Iowa .
#Text=“ I had been searching for a candidate with a consistent life ethic , a commitment to actively working for peace and justice , and concern for the environment ...
#Text=I will happily support you at the voting booth today . ” – Washington .

#Text=“ I was tired of not voting for someone , but rather against the other main candidate . ” -- Ohio “ My conscience will be clear when I leave the voting booth ... and I approve of this message . ” -- Georgia .
#Text=And from more short media takes on the campaign …
